s  offices worldwide avenue’s investment professionals seek good companies with bad balance sheets — firms with sustainable businesses and positive cash flow but whose financial situation is distressed the investment team uses avenue’s topdownbottomup approach to find undervalued opportunities and typically seeks to make nonoperational control investments in troubled businesses this provides the strategy maximum trading flexibility and allows avenue’s investment professionals to focus on preinvestment research and analysis rather than postinvestment operating issues from  to  chelsea clinton daughter of former president of the united states bill clinton and former secretary of state hillary clinton worked as an associate at avenue capital group llc bloomberg reported that as of february   avenue capital group is the th largest hedge fund in the world contents  history  ownership  corporate responsibility  references  external links historyedit avenue capital group was founded in  by siblings marc lasry and sonia gardner the two founders had previously founded amroc investments in  as a  million distressed debt investment fund organized in association with the robert m bass group in  mr lasry and ms gardner started their first avenue fund avenue investments with less than  million this onshore fund has grown to  million as of december   in  mr lasry and ms gardner formed their second avenue fund called avenue international this offshore fund attracts us tax exempt and nonus investors as of december   avenue international has  million in assets under management in  the firm was featured in maneet ahuja’s book the alpha masters unlocking the genius of the world’s top hedge funds in february  marc lasry explained on cnbc that avenue capital was taking advantage of the opportunity to purchase loans from european banks at a discount as lasry said most banks are being forced by the european central bank to sell loans and therefore were able to buy those loans at a great discount the ecb will likely continue to put pressure on these banks to clean up their balance sheet since its inception in  avenue has raised  private equity style investment funds across its three principal regions us europe and asia to invest in distressed securities and real estate united states   avenue special situations i   million   avenue special situations ii   million   avenue special situations iii   million   avenue special situations iv   billion   avenue real estate fund   million   avenue special situations v   billion   avenue special situations fund vi   billion    avenue energy opportunities fund   billion  asia   avenue asia capital partners   million   avenue asia special situations ii   million   avenue asia special situations iii   million   avenue asia special situations fund iv   billion europe   avenue europe special situations fund  € billion   avenue europe special situations fund ii –  billion avenue launched its asianfocused distressed business in  in  avenue launched its europeanfocused distressed business with rich furst as the senior portfolio manager while building distressed debt the european branch of the firm also writes loans for small companies that are unable to obtain financing ownershipedit in october  morgan stanley bought a noncontrolling  stake in the firm marc lasry and sonia gardner invested  of the proceeds they received from morgan stanley back into the avenue funds corporate responsibilityedit in  avenue capital group raised over  for herjustice a new yorkbased organisation devoted to ending domestic violence avenue capital group served as a sponsor in  and  and in july  avenue’s president sonia gardner hosted a breakfast on inmotion’s behalf to encourage other firms to participatenot in citation given ms gardner was again honored in  at the annual photography auction  benefit for her justice in january  marc lasry participated in portfolios with purpose in which participants compete on behalf of their favorite chariti